<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="9" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation 3A/611: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-29">January 29,
                                1944</date>.<lb/>[Received January 29—12:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>127. For Knapp<note n="25" xml:id="d9fn25">Laurence A. Knapp, Liaison
                                Officer between the United States and the Committee, and Special
                                Assistant to the Attorney General of the United States.</note> from
                            Spaeth. Yesterday Committee sent cable to Argentina expressing
                            satisfaction decision to break,<note n="26" xml:id="d9fn26">For
                                correspondence indicating United States interest in the break of
                                diplomatic relations between Argentina and the Axis, see <ref target="#pg_228">pp. 228</ref> ff.</note> noting decision <pb facs="0022" n="8" xml:id="pg_8"/> was taken because proof espionage
                            activities undermining national sovereignty and continental security and
                            expressing Committee’s desire collaborate with Argentina in study
                            measures common defense Continent against Axis political aggression.
                            [Spaeth.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>